result.name: Burger King - The Peak

reviews.text: Enjoy the views of Victoria Peak outside from indoors while having your hot meal.  Big dining area.
Burger king is burger king. Can't go wrong with Whopper.

Cheap, decent, fast food at a crowded tourist area. Can't expect much and there aren't many options, especially with The Peak mall being closed for renovation. 

It seemed a bit understaffed — the queue was long. Food tasted fine but our mushroom burger was DRENCHED in mayonnaise. Be sure to ask for less mayo!

3.5 stars
No good. Too expensive and small in portion. So not crowded. Only for tourist. For those prices, prefer Five Guys or Shake Shack in other places. Hope to see MacDon back to the Peak ASAP.
Long lines, very dirty with lots of trays on tables and overflowing trash. Once you order and pay, food is delivered immediately.
